%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20planter%20made%20with%20mosaic%20art.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500-300x224.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500-500x374.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500-150x112.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332386%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20large%20planter%20made%20with%20mosaic%20art.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEco-friendly%20aspects%20of%20their%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20is%20very%20particular%20that%20they%20do%20not%20destroy%20anything%20in%20nature.%20They%20do%20not%20support%20cutting%20down%20trees.%C2%A0%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20they%20use%20discarded%20driftwood%20and%20recycled%20timber%20%E2%80%93%20the%20two%20most%20environmentally-friendly%20ways%20to%20acquire%20wood.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20try%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20to%20salvage%20and%20upcycle%20our%20raw%20materials%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Yohann.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEvery%20few%20months%20they%20go%20to%20the%20beach%20at%20Gorai%20fishing%20village%20and%20pick%20up%20pieces%20of%20driftwood%20which%20they%20feel%20they%20can%20work%20with%20to%20make%20something%20beautiful.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaomi%20uses%20scrap%20and%20discarded%20materials%20like%20old%2C%20broken%20tiles%2C%20broken%20bangles%2C%20cracked%20vase%20pieces%2C%20pebbles%20and%20stones%2C%20beads%20and%20seashells%20in%20her%20mosaic%20art.%20Initially%2C%20she%20acquired%20sample%20tiles%20from%20shops.%20Her%20friends%20who%20knew%20of%20her%20work%20saved%20up%20their%20broken%20pieces%20of%20crockery%20and%20tiles%20remaining%20from%20renovation%20work%20for%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20the%20business%20has%20grown%2C%20she%20purchases%20broken%20tiles%20in%20bulk%20from%20sellers.%20In%20cases%20where%20the%20client%20wants%20a%20particular%20colour%20or%20design%20she%20buys%20tiles%20from%20stores.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20interesting%20raw%20material%20that%20she%20uses%20are%20the%20buoys%20in%20the%20sea.%20Made%20from%20fibre%20which%20is%20anti-corrosive%2C%20these%20buoys%C2%A0are%20being%20replaced%20by%20plastic%20ones%20these%20days%20by%20fishermen%20and%20are%20being%20discarded%20carelessly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaomi%20and%20Yohann%20then%20buy%20them%20from%20the%20fishermen%20to%20make%20planters%20embellished%20with%20mosaic%20or%20to%20build%20lotus%20ponds%20in%20which%20you%20can%20also%20put%20fish.%20The%20fibre%20is%20cleaned%2C%20refurbished%20and%20reused%20to%20make%20the%20signature%20planters%20or%20pond%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20adhere%20to%20our%20eco-friendly%20practices%20of%20minimum%20usage%20of%20chemicals%20on%20the%20wood.%20This%20way%2C%20it%20retains%20its%20natural%20beauty%20as%20well.%20We%20use%20linseed%20oil%20and%20tung%20oil%20as%20curing%20agents%20for%20protecting%20the%20wood%20and%20giving%20it%20a%20finish.%20However%2C%20we%20have%20to%20use%20an%20anti-termite%20solution%20to%20ensure%20the%20products%20are%20long-lasting.%20Otherwise%2C%20there%20is%20no%20point%20talking%20of%20sustainability%20if%20the%20products%20won%E2%80%99t%20last%20for%20the%20customer.%20We%20use%20machines%20to%20cut%20the%20wood%20but%20our%20products%20are%20hand%20polished%2C%E2%80%9D%20elaborates%20Yohann.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20wastage%20in%20the%20studio%20is%20kept%20to%20a%20minimum.%20Naomi%20collects%20the%20pieces%20that%20are%20left%20over%20from%20h